To run this project have node js installed somewhere on the machine, since the mongo database is cloud based there is no need to locally host it.
1. open the terminal in the same directory as the server.js file.
2. Type this command in the terminal and hit enter: "npm install express mongodb" 
3. Then type this command and hit enter: "node server"
4. In your web browser go to http://localhost:3000/
5. When you're finished use ctrl-c in the terminal to close the server.
